4300.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4300.description: SpongeBob and Patrick make a bet to see who can hold a "funny face" the longest...then their faces freeze that way! // SpongeBob and Patrick spend one last glorious - and dangerous - day at Glove World before it closes for good.

4303.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4303.description: There's a new Viking-themed promotion at the Krusty Krab, so SpongeBob is determined to find out everything there is to know about Vikings. And what better way to find out about Vikings than to talk to them himself? // Mermaidman and Barnacleboy are having a book signing, but SpongeBob can't go because he has boating school. After some convincing, Patrick finally gets SpongeBob to take a bathroom break from class.

4304.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4304.description: Mr. Krabs' granddad is coming to town! But instead of being excited, Mr. Krabs is nervous because his swarthy pirate granddad thinks that Mr. Krabs is a pirate, too. // When SpongeBob finds out that Squidward is a member of a secret society, SpongeBob decides he wants to join, too! The only problem is that the society is just for fish with tentacles.

4311.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4311.description: In the battle for fast food supremacy, Plankton has decided to throw in the towel and start a new business selling trinkets and souvenir gifts. He even renames his store from The Chum Bucket to The Chumporium. // Gary starts biting everyone in town, starting with Squidward. When Squid asks if Gary has been up-to-date on all of his snail shots, SpongeBob reveals that he's never done any of that before.

4312.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4312.description: Mr. Krabs is about to be fined for unfair labor practices. It turns out that in all the years he has been working at the Krusty Krab, SpongeBob has never taken a vacation. // SpongeBob finds an old powdered wig in the trash and wears it around town thinking it is the height of all things cool. The townspeople laugh at him, and Mr. Krabs makes him wear a ridiculous hairnet.

4313.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4313.description: When Squidward swallows his clarinet reed Sandy offers to retrieve the piece by shrinking herself and a mini sub down to microscopic proportions and traveling into Squid's body. // A misunderstanding over a vacation getaway advertisement causes Patrick to think he must "get out of town" or face dire consequences.

4327.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4327.description: SpongeBob eats some sea onion ice cream and his breath stinks. When people avoid him, Pat convinces SpongeBob that it's because he's ugly. // When Mr. Krabs gives his daughter Pearl a job at the Krusty krab, she starts to make some big changes in the menu and atmosphere. SpongeBob is threatened and doesn't like the new "management" but after a bit he gets used to it.

4328.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4328.description: Pat feels like he hasn't accomplished anything with his life and he decides to take SpongeBob on as his role model. At first, SpongeBob is flattered, but soon Pat takes the idea too far and begins to take over SpongeBob's life. // Pat's out of town and Spongebob is feeling lonely one day so he blows a bubble to keep him company. As he walks around town talking to his friend , everyone thinks he's taking this imaginary friend thing too far and needs help.

4329.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4329.description: When Squidward accidentally lets SpongeBob eat an exploding pie, he feels guilty and resolves to make SpongeBob's few remaining hours left in the world enjoyable. // Plankton schemes to steal the Krabby patty by disguising himself as Mr. Krabs and infiltrating the Krusty Krab.

4336.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4336.description: After receiving an invitation to a gallery opening, Squidward scrambles to find a friend to take with him. // While trying to order a special sandwich, Patrick gets swept up in the fast paced world of business.

4337.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4337.description: When SpongeBob cooks at home, Mr. Krabs' customers leave his restaurant and head for SpongeBob's Place. // When Plankton gets kicked out of the house, it's up to SpongeBob to teach him how to win his computer wife back.

4338.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4338.description: When stray snails start appearing around Bikini Bottom, SpongeBob decides to care for them himself. // To defend Bikini Bottom’s honor, Patrick enters a Krabby Patty eating competition.

4345.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4345.description: SpongeBob learns that "imitation is the sincerest form of flattery" - too bad no one told him how to stop! // When worms move in to SpongeBob's holes, it's up to him to hide his disgusting new friends from everyone else.

4346.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4346.description: SpongeBob brings home a box of new snail treats that Gary will do anything to get - especially when they run out. // Plankton wins a free Krabby Patty, and Mr. Krabs will do anything to stop him from collecting.

4347.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4347.description: Plankton teams up with Man Ray to take over the Krusty Krab and then-the world! Hahahahahaha! // Squidward quits the Krusty Krab to work for Plankton, turning the Chum Bucket into an overnight success.

4354.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4354.description: The Good Krabby Name: Mr. Krabs wants all of Bikini Bottom to eat at the Krusty Krab, so SpongeBob and Patrick go on an advertising blitz. Move It or Lose It: Mr. Krabs and Plankton circulate petitions to see which restaurant will get bulldozed by the city.

4355.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4355.description: SpongeBob and Patrick try to join the extreme sports team The Drasticals. // Sandy finds a book of world’s records, and tries to break them all with SpongeBob’s help.

4356.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4356.description: SpongeBob learns his milkshake license has expired, and is forced to go back to the milkshake academy. // Squidward hits his head and reverts to being a baby, and it's up to SpongeBob and Patrick to take care of him.

4364.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4364.description: Squidward finds SpongeBob's diary, and starts reading it out loud in the Krusty Krab. // SpongeBob once again fails his driving test, forcing Mrs. Puff to think outside the box--and off the road.

4365.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4365.description: An imprisoned Plankton teams up with his fellow inmates to break out of jail and steal the Krabby Patty secret formula. // SpongeBob replaces his broken spatula with one from Plankton, which may or may not have magical powers.

10398.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10398.description: When a volcanic vent under Goo Lagoon becomes active, a giant volatile gas bubble rises to the surface. Plankton manages to get his evil little hands on the bubble and threatens to pop it, covering all of Bikini Bottom in goo, unless Mr. Krabs gives him the Krabby Patty formula. It's up to SpongeBob, Patrick and Sandy to find a way to thwart Plankton and save the town

10401.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10401.description: SpongeBob is desperate to have Squidward visit him at home, but Squidward says there's no reason for him to come over, especially when he's perfectly comfortable in his own home. // All of SpongeBob's square pants have shrunk in the dryer. When he goes to the store to buy some more, he finds that the store is all out of square pants! With no other choice, SpongeBob decides to try a new look - round pants!

10402.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10402.description: Mermaidman and Barnacleboy are booked to attend a shuffleboarding tournament, but they can't go because they're laid up in the hospital. // When Squidward is mistaken for his much more famous rival, Squilliam Fancyson, he is invited to teach a class at the most prestigious music school in Bikini Bottom.

10409.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10409.description: After a freak bicycling accident, Squidward is coated in so much mud, leaves, and gunk to make him totally unrecognizable. The residents of Bikini Bottom think that Squidward is some sort of monster come to terrorize the town. // After practicing all day with his brand new magic kit, SpongeBob tries to impress Squidward with his newfound abilities. Of course Squidward, being the ever reluctant participant, sneaks away without SpongeBob noticing.

10410.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10410.description: SpongeBob has failed his driving test - again. Pat is so outraged by the injustice of it all that he storms into the testing facility and takes the test to prove that it is an unfair test and impossible to pass. // An oversight in a Royal genealogy document reveals that Patrick is the next in line to receive a kingly title. It's not long before the power of the crown goes straight to the starfish's head.

10411.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10411.description: SpongeBob's favorite jellyfishing net is missing! And worst of all, Pat may have been the one that stole it. // Rejected yet again by Squidward, SpongeBob decides that if he can't hang with the real Squid, he'll make his own. So SpongeBob builds a ventriloquist dummy modeled after his favorite neighbor.

10425.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10425.description: When Sandy goes out of town for a few days, she puts SpongeBob and Patrick in charge of her pet caterpillar. // Mr. Krabs keeps trying new sales gimmicks for the Krusty Krab, but none of them work. SpongeBob comes up with an idea for colored krabby patties, but Mr. Krabs scoffs at him reminding him to leave the creative thinking to him.

10426.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10426.description: When SpongeBob's grandma gives him a kiss in public, the guys at work tease him about being a little baby. // Squid is so sick and tired of living between SpongeBob and Pat that he decides to leave Bikini Bottom and go someplace where everyone is just like him.

10427.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10427.description: Sandy is going into hibernation in one week and she wants to pack a million activities for her and SpongeBob to do together in that short time. // Mr. Krabs tells SpongeBob and Pat that it's okay to borrow things as long as you put them back. So SpongeBob and Pat borrow a balloon from the Bargain Mart and they accidentally pop it.

10434.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10434.description: Patrick invents a new board game, and invites SpongeBob, Sandy and Squidward to play it with him. // After accidentally flushing Mr. Krabs’ safe, SpongeBob and Squidward must go into the sewers to find it.

10435.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10435.description: SpongeBob gets a pair of long pants, but they change his life in unexpected ways. // When Larry the Lobster opens a new gym in Bikini Bottom, SpongeBob becomes his best customer.

10436.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10436.description: Sandy tries to study SpongeBob and Patrick’s behavior, but her science experiment goes horribly awry. // Mr. Krabs takes Plankton’s advice, and finally marries the only thing he ever loved…money!

10443.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10443.description: Mr. Krabs gets trapped in Bikini Bottom’s brand-new bank, and it’s up to SpongeBob & Patrick to save him. // After failing again to steal the Krabby Patty formula, Plankton gets a pet to cheer himself up.

10444.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10444.description: SpongeBob and Patrick go to see the latest horror film, only to be seemingly stalked by the villain. // SpongeBob holds a séance at the Krusty Krab to learn the recipe for a long-lost sandwich.

10445.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10445.description: SpongeBob will do anything to get to meet his newest hero, Kenny The Cat. // Attempting to get more work out of Squidward, Mr. Krabs spins the story of the monstrous Yeti Crab, which eats lazy workers.

10452.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10452.description: In order to save money, Mr. Krabs fires SpongeBob. Unable to just “do nothing”, SpongeBob decides to go back to work doing anything, anywhere.

10453.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
10453.description: SpongeBob tries to take a shortcut to work, but becomes lost along the way. // After failing his driver’s test again, Mr. Krabs decides to teach SpongeBob how to drive himself.

16954.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16954.description: SpongeBob adopts a stray worm, and to his surprise, the worm gives birth to some worm babies overnight! But since Gary won’t play nice, SpongeBob needs to find loving homes for his new slimey, weird-looking friends. // Plankton is sick of Karen’s criticisms, so he decides he can just replace her with some new computer inventions! But when he takes them out on a Krabby Patty formula-stealing mission, he learns that Karen truly is one of a kind.

16955.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16955.description: SpongeBob is left in charge of the Krusty Krab while Mr. Krabs steps out for 15 minutes, and he is determined to make it the best-managed 15 minutes ever! / SpongeBob's got a full day, and he's determined to do everything he's scheduled to do: help fix Mr. Krabs' telescope, go to Patrick's birthday party, and help with Sandy's science presentation.

16962.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16962.description: Mr. Krabs and Plankton have been business rivals and bitter enemies for longer than anyone can remember. But one day, Mr. Krabs reveals that they were not always this way. There was a time when the two rivals were best friends.

16963.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16963.description: Mr. Krab's old fry cook pays a special visit to the Krusty Krab. SpongeBob is in awe of his predecessor, who has since become a world renowned chef following his departure from Krabs' restaurant. // Tales of the boogeyman sends SpongeBob into panic. Every dark corner in his house could be a potential hiding place for the infamous monster.

16964.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16964.description: Determined to uncover Plankton’s next devious plot, Mr. Krabs sends SpongeBob and Patrick to spy on him. // Watch an instructional video on boating techniques with Squidward and SpongeBob. // Mr. Krabs holds a contest for his employees: The first one to learn the names of every Krusty Krab customer wins a tropical vacation.

16978.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16978.description: SpongeBob and Pat are fascinated by the snow they see inside the Treedome and want to play in it, but sandy is hibernating for the winter. // One day, Gary starts following Pat around and SpongeBob can't figure out why. At first, it doesn't bother him, but slowly he grows more and more jealous and becomes determined to win Gary back.

16979.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16979.description: SpongeBob attempts and fails his driving test again, but a ragged and fed up Ms. Puff wants him out of her classroom so she makes up some bogus extra credit for him so he can pass the test. // When SpongeBob and Pat go to a jellyfishing convention, SpongeBob tries to join an exclusive, elitist jellyfishing club. Secretly, the club president thinks SpongeBob is not worthy.

16980.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16980.description: When Mermaid Man and Barnacle Boy go away for the weekend, they ask SpongeBob and Pat to house sit for them. Inside the house, SpongeBob and Pat discover the evil super villain, Man-Ray frozen in a tank. // SpongeBob becomes an overnight stand up comedy sensation when he starts telling derogatory jokes about squirrels. At first, Sandy is a good sport, but soon people start treating her as if she really was stupid and smelly.

16987.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16987.description: Pearl gets a job to be cool like her friends, but the only store that’s hiring is the lamest store at the mall! // SpongeBob loses the use of his thumbs, and must get them back in working order before his entire life falls apart.

16988.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16988.description: 'The Sharks' are the toughest guys in town, but their next confrontation might be too much for SpongeBob to handle. // Plankton clones SpongeBob in an effort to steal Krabs’ secret formula, but original Bob might ruin his plans.

16989.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16989.description: When SpongeBob and Patrick think their homes have been sold, they move away - much to Squidward’s delight. // When fortune cookies start predicting the future, Plankton realizes he can twist them to his own evil schemes.

16456.description: Pearl and Narlene have a whales' day out in the big city.

16457.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16457.description: Mr. Krabs and Plankton must work together after discovering a well of miracle-grease under their restaurants.

17007.description: Sandy creates the latest acorn-based food sensation, but her tree pays the price for her greed. // SpongeBob erects a community bulletin board in the Krusty Krab, but anonymous reviews posted on it lead to trouble.

17015.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
17015.description: The gang heads to a food convention, but things go awry when they become stranded in the woods. // SpongeBob accidentally fibs to his pen pal, but when his friend comes to visit, he must keep the ruse going!

17016.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
17016.description: When SpongeBob hides the secret formula in his home, it’s up to Gary to protect it from Plankton. // When a freak accident causes everyone in town to become as stupid as Patrick, Sandy must save the day.

23521.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
23521.description: When a storm sweeps the Krusty Krab away, its crew and customers will need a crazed Krabs to lead them back home. // Patrick’s last baby tooth needs to come out, but he’s afraid to let it go.

23524.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
23524.description: Patrick is sick of all of his friends not being able to play with him because they have to put on their Krusty Krab hats and go to work. // A new toy store has opened up in Bikini Bottom, and SpongeBob and Patrick couldn’t be happier! In fact, they are having so much fun at the toy store that they accidentally get locked in when it closes.

23525.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
23525.description: A friendly day of building sand castles soon turns into all out war when SpongeBob and Patrick use their sand creations to battle each other. // Gary desperately needs a new shell, but all the shells on the market are either too expensive or too fragile. And when SpongeBob tries to find other alternatives to real shells, nothing else seems to work.

23532.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
23532.description: After arriving one minute late for work, SpongeBob decides to move into the Krusty Krab so that he will never be late to work again. // When Plankton secretly turns down the thermostat at the Krusty Krab the entire restaurant freezes over. But with a couple of frozen Krabby Patties tied to his shoes for skates, SpongeBob turns the frozen floor into an ice rink

23533.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
23533.description: The scariest roller coaster ever has just opened at Bikini Bottom's amusement park. At first SpongeBob and Patrick are determined to ride it, but the more they think about how scary it is the more they chicken out. // Plankton tricks SpongeBob, Patrick and Squidward into fixing up the Chum Bucket.

23534.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
23534.description: SpongeBob has trouble saying Goodbye to the most perfect Krabby Patty he has ever cooked up. // After electrocuting himself on his own security fence, Squidward’s personality gets completely scrambled. Now he is the most jovial Squid to ever live in Bikini Bottom – and he’s starting to get on everyone’s nerves.

23548.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
23548.description: Sandy and SpongeBob get into a fierce competition doing extreme underwater sports. The longer they compete, the more people they attract and soon SpongeBob has a small following who cheer him on. // SpongeBob and Pat visit the zoo and SpongeBob innocently toses a peanut at an oyster in order to rouse it. The oyster goes crazy and suddenly the authorities demand to know what could have caused this.

23549.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
23549.description: SpongeBob and Patrick disturb the Flying Dutchman's slumber and he turns them into ghosts. // Squidward and SpongeBob have to share a locker.

23550.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
23550.description: Mr. Krabs loses SpongeBob's fry cook contract in a bet with Plankton and SpongeBob is forced to go work at the Chum Bucket. While there, SpongeBob is so homesick that he can't even fry up a single patty. // When SpongeBob and Pat discover a pencil from the surface they begin to draw with it. Everything they draw, comes to life! Soon, they begin to do small, lame pranks on the neighbors.

23566.description: SpongeBob and Patrick get hooked on the latest fad - flying your own brain like a tiny drone! // When SpongeBob & Patrick play Mermaidman and Barnacleboy, it's all fun and games until their sworn enemies arrive!

23567.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
23567.description: When SpongeBob thinks he's allergic to his pineapple, Squidward offers to help find him a new home. // Squidward is getting a nose job at the local hospital, and SpongeBob tags along as moral support.

23568.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
23568.description: Squidward is so tired that SpongeBob & Patrick can't wake him up, but they won't let him miss his big audition! // Mr. Krabs & his crew cater a fancy party, but they might be out of their depth with their new wealthy customers.

22968.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
22968.description: Frustrated that he's seen as cute instead of evil, Plankton builds a robot to punish anyone who says "aww!"

22969.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
22969.description: Karen tells the fairytale of a nerd trying to steal an action figure from his three little neighbors.

23575.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
23575.description: After a misunderstanding, SpongeBob and Patrick try to prove their life insurance protects them from any danger! // When SpongeBob blows himself a bubble boat, everyone in town wants one! Everyone except Mrs. Puff, that is.

23576.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
23576.description: Plankton closes the Chum Bucket and moves to a new town, but Mr. Krabs suspects he's still up to no good. // When SpongeBob accidentally picks up Neptune's magic trident, there's no telling what trouble he may cause!

23577.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
23577.description: SpongeBob must figure out how to do his job after accidentally shrinking himself. // Squidward invents a new sport to get back at SpongeBob and Patrick for annoying him.

23585.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
23585.description: When SpongeBob mistakes an escaped convict for his driving instructor, it's the new teacher who learns a lesson. // When Krabs sends him searching for a missing toy, SpongeBob finds himself lost... in the lost & found!

23586.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
23586.description: Patrick has a coupon for free ice cream, but he'll have to get to the store if he wants to use it! // Krabs buys Squidward's art, but to make a profit on his purchase he'll have to get the artist out of the picture!

29953.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
29953.description: When a prehistoric Sponge is unfrozen, he causes chaos all over town - and only SpongeBob can communicate with him! // When a flock of clams descend on Bikini Bottom, SpongeBob has to get them out before they ruin the whole town!

29956.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
29956.description: Plankton hires Patrick to create advertising slogans for the Chum Bucket. // SpongeBob helps Plankton find the perfect anniversary gift for Karen.

29957.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
29957.description: Squidward gets stuck indoors with SpongeBob and Patrick during a storm. // Plankton creates an underground restaurant that threatens to put the Krusty Krab out of business.

29964.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
29964.description: Mr. Krabs makes a wish that he could talk to money. When his wish is magically granted, Krabs learns (to his horror) what all of his dollars, pennies and quarters have been longing for: they want Krabs to spend them. // Squidward trains SpongeBob for the Bikini Bottom dance contest.

29965.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
29965.description: SpongeBob becomes the latest local obsession after a notable food critic gives him high ratings. Now Mr. Krabs is looking to cash in on the fad by making everything in the Krusty Krab Sponge-themed. // SpongeBob helps Patrick get his song some air time at the local radio station.

29966.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
29966.description: SpongeBob and Patrick try to help Sandy rid her Tree Dome of fleas. // When Patrick accidentally takes SpongeBob’s donut he is wracked with guilt over his heinous crime. // SpongeBob battles a persistent speck of food that is on a plate.

29967.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
29967.description: SpongeBob and Patrick fall into a cavern where frightful Trenchbillies keep them hostage. // Squidward's complaints trigger a volcanic eruption.

29981.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
29981.description: Pat has a box and he won't show SpongeBob what's inside of it because it's a secret. SpongeBob can't believe Pat would keep something from him and he pretends not to care what's inside, but secretly it's driving him crazy. // Squidward's old High School rival comes to town and brags to Squid about his famous marching band. Feeling outdone, Squid lies and says he has a band, too.

29982.title: SpongeBob SquarePants

He recruits SpongeBob to help him woo Ms. Puff. SpongeBob tries to play match maker, but he screws it all up and Krabs threatens his job!

Spongebob offers to act stupid next to Pat in front of Patricks' parents in order to make Pat look smarter.

29999.description: When his pet amoeba Spot has puppies, Plankton decides to use them in another of his nefarious plots. // Mr. Krabs is too scared to get his physical, but if he doesn't pass, the Krusty Krab will be shut down!

30000.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
30000.description: Plankton poses as a wish-granting genie in his latest scheme to get the secret formula. // Mr. Krabs' new Krabby soup is a hit - until some heat-loving hippies move into the soup vat!

30001.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
30001.description: When Man Ray rents Squidward's house for the weekend, it's up to SpongeBob and Patrick to stop his evil vacation! // Mr. Krabs takes a vacation and makes Larry the Lobster the temporary manager of the Krusty Krab.

29507.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
29507.description: Patrick crushes the mailman, so he and SpongeBob deliver the mail around Bikini Bottom.

29508.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
29508.description: Squidward hosts a secret "We Hate SpongeBob Club" at his house.

30008.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
30008.description: Patrick leads an enthusiastic stranger on a tour of his favorite places in Bikini Bottom. // SpongeBob is afraid to get off the roof of the Krusty Krab, but he won't let that stop him from living his life!

30009.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
30009.description: A new secret Krabby Patty formula has disastrous results for Bikini Bottom, and only SpongeBob can save the day. // Mr. Krabs and Plankton have to take boating school classes. Thankfully, SpongeBob's there to show them the ropes!

30010.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
30010.description: When his clarinet goes missing, Squidward must become a hardboiled detective to track it down. // Squidward sends SpongeBob and Patrick on an increasingly difficult scavenger hunt to get them out of his hair.

30018.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
30018.description: SpongeBob's new friend is a giant fluffy hamster. There's one problem, though: no one else can see him! // Patrick wants to be a horse!

30019.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
30019.description: Gary has a pet translation collar, and he's talking up a storm. Everyone loves it... except for Squidward! // When a small clown gets left behind by the circus, SpongeBob takes the hapless harlequin under his wing.

30020.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
30020.description: SpongeBob can't drive, but you don't need a license to operate a self-driving car! // Patrick thinks he's an old man, so it's up to SpongeBob to remind him how much fun being a kid can be!

36685.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36685.description: King Neptune is celebrating his birthday at the Krusty Krab, and SpongeBob wants to make sure all his friends and family are there, including his son, Triton.

36686.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36686.description: Squidward becomes the star of his own public access TV show. // Squidward tries to sabotage SpongeBob's big dance audition.

36693.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36693.description: Plankton creates a gas that turns everyone at the Krusty Krab into babies. // After being enrolled in a chef exchange program, SpongeBob switches places with a snooty French chef from a high-end restaurant.

36694.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36694.description: It’s Picture Day for the Boating School Year Book, and SpongeBob has spent all morning getting ready for it. Now all he has to do is make it to Boating School without getting dirty. // When Patrick eats his weight in Krabby Patties without paying, Mr. Krabs puts him to work in the restaurant. // SpongeBob’s parents are missing. All clues of their whereabouts point to his nefarious cousin Blackjack, the family bully who used to torment SpongeBob when they were little.

36695.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36695.description: While trying to wrestle open the cap off of a tube of toothpaste SpongeBob accidentally punches himself in the face leaving behind a hideous black eye. // Plankton has brainwashed Mermaid Man and Barnacle Boy! With the dynamic duo under Plankton’s control, he orders them to wreak havoc on the Krusty Krab. It’s up to SpongeBob SquarePants and his trusty spatula to save the day!

36709.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36709.description: SpongeBob reads a "bad" word off the dumpster behind the Krusty Krabs and he doesn't know what it means. He asks Pat who explains to him that it's a fancy word and both of them start using it in every sentence they can. // When eager Spongebob enrolls in Squidward's community art class, arrogant Squidward attempts to teach Spongebob strictly by the book.

36710.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36710.description: When money hungry Mr. Krabs discovers that customers love Spongebob's special jellyfish jelly Krabby Patty, he convinces Spongebob to bring him as many of the jellyfish as he can. // Krabs enters SpongeBob in the athletic competition - the Fry Cook Games. SpongeBob is thrilled and starts to train hard. When Pat wants to train as well, SpongeBob tells him you have to be a fry cook to compete.

36711.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36711.description: Believing Mr. Krab is taking advantage, Squidward convinces na´ve Spongebob to join with him and threaten to a strike. When Mr. Krabs fires them both, a frustrated Squidward tries to teach Spongebob the art of picketing. // A large worm is terrorizing Bikini Bottom and SpongeBob is terrified of it. Sandy thinks he is a chicken and drags him out into the wilderness to take the worm on. When they finally see the worm, it turns out SpongeBob was right.

36718.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36718.description: Squidward is so tired that SpongeBob & Patrick can't wake him up, but they won't let him miss his big audition! // Mr. Krabs & his crew cater a fancy party, but they might be out of their depth with their new wealthy customers.

36719.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36719.description: After a misunderstanding, SpongeBob and Patrick try to prove their life insurance protects them from any danger! // When SpongeBob blows himself a bubble boat, everyone in town wants one! Everyone except Mrs. Puff, that is.

36720.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36720.description: Plankton closes the Chum Bucket and moves to a new town, but Mr. Krabs suspects he's still up to no good. // When SpongeBob accidentally picks up Neptune's magic trident, there's no telling what trouble he may cause!

36727.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36727.description: SpongeBob and Patrick exchange tiny living versions of themselves. It's a whole hunk of homunculus fun! // Plankton tells his Grandma that he owns the Krusty Krab, but must keep the lie going when she comes to visit.

36728.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36728.description: SpongeBob and Patrick become trapped in an alternate dimension where anything they draw comes to life. // SpongeBob and Patrick help Bubble Bass move out of his mother's basement.

36729.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36729.description: SpongeBob wants to be the first sponge to dive all the way up to the surface of the ocean! // When SpongeBob and Squidward accidentally let Plankton steal the secret formula, it's up to them to steal it back!

35982.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
35982.description: Plankton joins the League of E.V.I.L.

36736.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36736.description: Now that Fred's leg has healed up, SpongeBob is determined to keep it out of harm's way...no matter what! // Patrick's lemonade stand isn't doing too well...until he gets a secret ingredient from Squidward!

36737.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36737.description: When The Krusty Krab runs out of mustard, Mr. Krabs sends SpongeBob, Patrick and Squidward to dig up some more! // SpongeBob and Sandy have to collect Krabby Patty ingredients, but Plankton is following their every step.

36738.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36738.description: Mr. Krabs hires Squidward to babysit Pearl for the night, but she just wants to sneak out to a cool teen party! // After spilling a milkshake during a delivery, SpongeBob vows to return and clean the entire building!

36746.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36746.description: Plankton tells Patrick he's his conscience so he can convince the wooden-headed star to steal him a Krabby Patty. // When Mr. Krabs puts in an open kitchen, SpongeBob gets stage fright and has to invent a new persona.

36747.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
36747.description: Plankton hasn't tried to steal the secret formula in a while...and that's making Mr. Krabs nervous! // When Patrick discovers the pineapple's library, SpongeBob introduces him to the wonderful world of book learning!

43354.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43354.description: Plankton goes to jail, but the secret formula is taken as evidence! SpongeBob and Mr. Krabs plot to get it back. // Sandy struggles to build a ship-in-a-bottle before a big contest, so SpongeBob calls in a little extra help.

43357.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43357.description: Mr. Krabs tries to find enough food to feed Pearl as she goes through her growth spurt. // After showering, SpongeBob gets stuck in his wringer.

43358.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43358.description: Plankton steals Sandy's fur to disguise himself as Sandy and get the Krabby Patty formula. // Plankton goes inside SpongeBob's head to get the Krabby Patty formula.

43365.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43365.description: Instead of getting on the ship headed for summer camp, SpongeBob and Patrick accidentally board a ship full of prisoners on their way to jail on Inferno Island. // SpongeBob and Pat stow away on one of Sandy’s extreme wilderness expeditions. But when they get accidentally left behind, they must band together in order to survive in the wild.

43366.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43366.description: While researching his family tree SpongeBob discovers that he was related to the great Western hero, and famous chili-slinger, SpongeBuck.

43367.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43367.description: SpongeBob and Mr. Krabs turn an old submarine into a mobile Krusty Krab. Not to be undone by his competitor’s new gimmick, Plankton responds with his own traveling Chum Bucket. // When Patrick and SpongeBob discover they have clashing views on cleanliness, their disagreement blows up into an epic battle. Is it possible for a soap-lover like SpongeBob to ever be friends with a dirt-monger like Patrick?

43381.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43381.description: Plankton has a new invention that allows him to switch lives with Mr. Krabs. He is so excited because once he has Mr. Krabs' life, he will also have the Krabby Patty secret formula. // When Larry the Lobster is short one man for lifeguard duty, SpongeBob volunteers. Larry describes all the perks of the jobs: tanning, the whistle, the attention. What SpongeBob doesn't get is that you have to be able to swim.

43382.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43382.description: SpongeBob and Patrick build a small clubhouse in a tree and get inside. When Squid comes by they tell him he can't join the club because he wouldn't fit in. Upset, Squid insists on joining and climbs the tree and gets inside. // SpongeBob finds a stray sea horse and adopts it. When it comes time to go to work, SpongeBob can't bear to leave him at home so he takes him to work and hides him in the kitchen.

43383.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43383.description: When SpongeBob learns that Squid has never actually tried a Krabby Patty, he becomes obsessed with the idea that Squid must try it. // There is a new bully in boating school named Flats who threatens to beat SpongeBob up after school. SpongeBob is terrified and tries to get help, but everyone is under Flats terror hold already

43390.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43390.description: SpongeBob must figure out how to do his job after accidentally shrinking himself. // Squidward invents a new sport to get back at SpongeBob and Patrick for annoying him.

43391.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43391.description: When SpongeBob mistakes an escaped convict for his driving instructor, it's the new teacher who learns a lesson. // When Krabs sends him searching for a missing toy, SpongeBob finds himself lost... in the lost & found!

43392.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43392.description: Patrick has a coupon for free ice cream, but he'll have to get to the store if he wants to use it! // Krabs buys Squidward's art, but to make a profit on his purchase he'll have to get the artist out of the picture!

43399.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43399.description: The long-lost episode of Mermaid Man is finally showing on TV, but will SpongeBob make it home in time to watch? // Karen gets a computer virus, and it's up to SpongeBob to get it out of her!

43400.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43400.description: When a gang of kids steals the Krusty Krab's grill, SpongeBob and Mr. Krabs go to extreme lengths to win it back. // SpongeBob helps out the Krusty Krab's night shift crew, but the customers crave something creepier than usual.

43401.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43401.description: SpongeBob visits his old pal Bubble Buddy's hometown... Bubbletown! // Sandy invites Karen and Mrs. Puff out for a night on the town, so the ladies decide to blow off some steam.

42647.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
42647.description: SpongeBob and Patrick take Squidward on a plane to a tropical resort.

43408.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43408.description: SpongeBob and Patrick have their peaceful day of jelly fishing disturbed by Sandy's competitive nature. // SpongeBob pulls from Squidward's shirt a loose string that never seems to end.

43409.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43409.description: Encouraged by his best friend, Patrick Starfish, SpongeBob overcomes his fears and finally applies for that dream job as a fry cook at the Krusty Krab. // Finding the perfect use for his electric, high powered reef blower, SpongeBob goes to work. Squidward has no idea what chaos lay in store for his quiet afternoon at home. // When SpongeBob meets Sandy Cheeks for the first time, she invites him over to her glass enclosed home. SpongeBob finds the bio dome is full of air, something he's never experienced before.

43410.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43410.description: SpongeBob introduces Patrick and Squidward to his unique talent, the art of bubble blowing. After first turning his nose up at this plebeian pastime, Squidward accepts the challenge and attempts to surpass SpongeBob's skill. // When SpongeBob tries to impress Sandy Cheeks at Mussel Beach, he accidentally rips his pants. SpongeBob is embarrassed until he realizes the beach crowd thought he jokingly did it on purpose.

43418.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43418.description: When SpongeBob and Patrick find Squidward is recovering from a bicycling accident, SpongeBob and Patrick decide to take Squidward jellyfishing with them so that he can have his "best day ever." // SpongeBob falls victim to a scheme by the evil Plankton, Mr. Krabs' arch-rival with the Napoleon complex. Plankton hides out in SpongeBob's head and takes control of his brain.

43419.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43419.description: In order to get peace and quiet, Squidward plays a cruel joke on SpongeBob and Patrick which makes the two believe they are no longer friends. // It's exam time again at Mrs. Puff's Boating School. SpongeBob, in his never ending quest to pass the boat driving section of the exam, turns to Patrick for help.

43420.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
43420.description: Mr. Krabs has SpongeBob and Squidward go above and beyond the call of duty to make the first successful Krabby Patty pizza delivery. // Losing his pineapple house to parasites, SpongeBob finds himself relying on his neighbors in order to remain in his neighborhood. After disastrous stays with Patrick and Squidward, SpongeBob must move back with his parents.

49567.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49567.description: Mr. Krabs and Plankton woo customers with greasy entrees. // SpongeBob tries a career at being a model in a kitchen sponge commercial.

49568.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49568.description: Squidward cleans up the city of Bikini Bottom with "help" from SpongeBob. // SpongeBob brings Gary a pet that terrorizes him.

49575.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49575.description: When SpongeBob tries to spend some quality time with his friends, he just ends up being a nuisance to everyone instead. They all tell him to go away, so with a heavy heart, SpongeBob decides to do just that.

49576.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49576.description: Squidward is rushed to the hospital when SpongeBob accidentally slams the door on Squidward’s face. He undergoes surgery to have his face fixed to look normal again – but things don’t go exactly as planned. // A very windy day in Bikini Bottom is blowing air through SpongeBob’s holes resulting in a chorus of pretty flute-like sounds. This attracts all the local Jellyfish who love the music coming out of SpongeBob.

49577.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49577.description: SpongeBob loves Krabby Patties so much, he just can't help singing and dancing when he's around the delicious sandwiches. // When Stanley, SpongeBob's klutzy, absent-minded cousin, comes to visit Bikini Bottom, he quickly turns SpongeBob's life upside down.

49591.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49591.description: SpongeBob and Patrick dig a tunnel between their two houses and drive Squidward nuts. // Pat learns just enough karate to wreak havoc in Bikini Bottom.

49592.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49592.description: Mermaid Man and Barnacle Boy are eating at the Krusty Krab when Mermaid Man accidentally drops his utility belt. SpongeBob finds the belt and can’t resist it. // During a boating lesson with Mrs. Puff, SpongeBob loses control of his boat and crashes it into a juice truck and a senior citizens home. Mrs. Puff confesses that she is responsible for SpongeBob, so the police throw her in jail.

49593.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49593.description: When it snows in Bikini Bottom, SpongeBob and Pat go out in the snow and play in their snow forts etc… They make a racket and Squid complains. Squid makes fun of them for playing in the snow. // When Mr. Krabs has a garage sale and tries to sell everyone’s trash as priceless heirlooms, he ends up selling Spongebob a novelty soda drink hat, which to Krabs’s surprise turns out to be the most popular item in Bikini Bottom.

49600.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49600.description: When a prehistoric Sponge is unfrozen, he causes chaos all over town - and only SpongeBob can communicate with him! // When a flock of clams descend on Bikini Bottom, SpongeBob has to get them out before they ruin the whole town!

49601.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49601.description: When his pet amoeba Spot has puppies, Plankton decides to use them in another of his nefarious plots. // Mr. Krabs is too scared to get his physical, but if he doesn't pass, the Krusty Krab will be shut down!

49602.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49602.description: Plankton poses as a wish-granting genie in his latest scheme to get the secret formula. // Mr. Krabs' new Krabby soup is a hit - until some heat-loving hippies move into the soup vat!

49609.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49609.description: Watching their favorite show, reruns of the TV duo superhero show Mermaid Man and Barnacle Boy, SpongeBob and Patrick hear that their beloved heroes are living in a nearby retirement home. // SpongeBob loses his self-confidence when an arrogant customer wrongfully claims SpongeBob forgot to put pickles on his Krabby Patty. With his perfect record now ruined, SpongeBob quits his job.

49610.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49610.description: It's time to pick this weeks Hall Monitor at Mrs. Puff's Boating School and much to her dismay, it's SpongeBob's turn. The overzealous SpongeBob assumes the authority and extends it's jurisdiction beyond the school yard. // Over the repeated warning of his friends, SpongeBob takes a wild jellyfish home from JellyFish Fields. To his dismay, SpongeBob discovers that jellyfish multiply quickly, and they take over his house.

49611.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49611.description: Sandy Cheeks has taken on the inevitable mission of taking a rocket ship into outer space. Sneaking in for a look, SpongeBob and Patrick accidentally launch Sandy's rocket and mistakenly think they have landed on the moon. // Mr. Krabs gives SpongeBob a pair of squeaky boots in lieu of pay. No problem. SpongeBob loves them and learns to master the squeaking noise to a new height of communication.

49618.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49618.description: When the mysterious "hooks" (fishing, that is) suddenly appear in Bikini Bottom, Mr. Krabs warns SpongeBob to stay away from them. // SpongeBob wins the big prize from his favorite TV show, "The Adventures of Mermaid Man and Barnacle Boy" - The Conch Signal! Now he can summon the semi-retired super heroes whenever there's an emergency.

49619.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49619.description: There's a talent show at the Krusty Krab and Squidward takes over the planning. SpongeBob, wanting to do his part as well as impress his parents, offers to do anything. // After another failed attempt by the evil Plankton to steal a Krusty Krabs' Krabby Patty, SpongeBob reasons that Plankton is just lonely and needs a friend.

49620.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49620.description: SpongeBob finds Sandy Squirrel's rigorous physical training program too tough and chooses the easy way out by ordering a pair of fake "bulky arms" as seen on TV. // SpongeBob and Patrick accidentally hit Squidward with a flying shell, thinking they knocked him out. They place what is really a wax replica next to the heater, melting him.

49628.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49628.description: When Mr. Krab's daughter Pearl is stood up for her prom, SpongeBob agrees to step in. // Mr. Krabs uses the award to drive SpongeBob, but he dupes SpongeBob into believing he might break his ongoing winning streak and lose this month to Squidward.

49629.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
49629.description: Fleeing from SpongeBob and Patrick's incessant noise, Squidward winds up frozen in the Krusty Krab freezer. When he finally does thaw out, he finds himself far into the future, unable to get home and actually missing SpongeBob. // SpongeBob and Sandy's incessant Karate sparring is starting to wreak havoc in the Krusty Krab. Mr. Krabs orders SpongeBob, under penalty of being fired, to cease all Karate activities.

55810.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55810.description: One night, SpongeBob suddenly possesses the amazing ability to visit the dreams of his friends and neighbors. As he visits from one dream to the next, SpongeBob gets involved in their personal fantasies, for better or worse. // SpongeBob comes down with a case of the dreaded "Suds", an illness which turns him into a sniffly, sneezing, bubble-maker.

55813.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55813.description: SpongeBob and Patrick buy a toy and have to learn to share it. // SpongeBob goes with Mr. Krabs to the Cheapest Crab Convention.

55814.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55814.description: SpongeBob and Patrick protest the construction of a highway that would destroy Jellyfish Fields.

55821.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55821.description: When Squidward sees Squilliam on a TV show about fancy homes, Squidward becomes infuriated and tries to outdo him. // When SpongeBob mistakenly thinks that Plankton is starting a band, Plankton decides to use this to his advantage.

55822.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55822.description: When Mr. Krabs sees SpongeBob pick something up off the street, he begins to obsess over the idea that SpongeBob found a penny - a penny that he should have found first! // SpongeBob's boating school class is going on a field trip.

55823.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55823.description: Plankton has demolished the Chum Bucket! In its place, he has built a Roman coliseum. // The Bikini Bottom Symphony is accepting submissions for their composition contest, and Squidward is determined to win.

55837.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55837.description: Krabs makes a low budget commercial and SpongeBob is in it for one second. After the commercial airs once at three in the morning, a blind man recognizes SpongeBob. // Squid is fed up with Krab’s insults and he quits, bragging about how easy it will be to find another job. But of course, it’s not and Squid falls upon hard times. He goes though all his savings and is dirt poor.

55838.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55838.description: SpongeBob and Sandy are enjoying a day at the beach when they come across the Salty Spitoon, a rough and tumble hangout for real rugged folk. Sandy makes it through the bouncer, but SpongeBob is left outside. // Squidward's arch nemesis, Squilliam, has returned to harass Squidward on his failed life since high school. Squidward lies and tells him that he actually owns a five star restaurant.

55839.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55839.description: SpongeBob and Patrick are wreaking havoc on the Krusty Krab, so Mr. Krabs decides to give them a little busy work. He tells them to paint his living room, and gives them permanent paint. Very permanent. // The excitement! You are now a member of the official Krusty Krab crew! In this informative episode, you will learn all of the attributes necessary to become an excellent employee in the world of fast food restaurants.

55846.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55846.description: When Man Ray rents Squidward's house for the weekend, it's up to SpongeBob and Patrick to stop his evil vacation! // Mr. Krabs takes a vacation and makes Larry the Lobster the temporary manager of the Krusty Krab.

55847.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55847.description: Patrick leads an enthusiastic stranger on a tour of his favorite places in Bikini Bottom. // SpongeBob is afraid to get off the roof of the Krusty Krab, but he won't let that stop him from living his life!

55848.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55848.description: A new secret Krabby Patty formula has disastrous results for Bikini Bottom, and only SpongeBob can save the day. // Mr. Krabs and Plankton have to take boating school classes. Thankfully, SpongeBob's there to show them the ropes!

55855.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55855.description: It's Valentine's Day and SpongeBob has made an extra special Valentine for his best friend in the world, Patrick Starfish. Disaster strikes when the present doesn't show up as planned and Patrick feels snubbed, to say the least! // When Squidward discards what to him is a worthless gum wrapper, SpongeBob teaches him that one man's useless piece of paper can be another man's magical toy.

55856.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55856.description: SpongeBob and Patrick convince Mr. Krabs to join in a friendly board game of "Treasure Hunt". Even a pretend search for gold proves too alluring for Mr. Krabs, who convinces the two lads to join him on a real treasure hunt. // SpongeBob accidentally gets on the wrong bus, he finds himself lost in an unfamiliar and mysterious part of the sea called Rock Bottom.

55857.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55857.description: Sandy Squirrel comes down with a case of the blues and SpongeBob is determined to find out why and what he can do about it. // The evil Plankton is up to no good once again when he tries to manipulate SpongeBob into becoming aggressive and mean in order to get more out of life.

55864.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55864.description: Its April Fools Day, one of SpongeBob's favorite days of the year because he gets to play harmless pranks all day long (even if most people don't get them). // On a visit to the Fry Cook Hall of Fame, SpongeBob inadvertently pulls a mythical spatula from a vat of ancient grease, thus giving him claim to the title of "Worlds Greatest Fry Cook".

55865.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55865.description: Pat gets a new pair of shoes, but doesn't know how to tie his laces. When SpongeBob offers to demonstrate lace tying to Pat , he forgets how to do it. // Mr. Krabs takes the day off from the Krusty Krab and puts Squid in charge for the day. Squid seizes the opportunity to take the day off as well and he leaves SpongeBob alone to man the store.

55866.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55866.description: SpongeBob eats some sea onion ice cream and his breath stinks. When people avoid him, Pat convinces SpongeBob that it's because he's ugly. // When Mr. Krabs gives his daughter Pearl a job at the Krusty krab, she starts to make some big changes in the menu and atmosphere. SpongeBob is threatened and doesn't like the new "management" but after a bit he gets used to it.

55874.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55874.description: Pat feels like he hasn't accomplished anything with his life and he decides to take SpongeBob on as his role model. At first, SpongeBob is flattered, but soon Pat takes the idea too far and begins to take over SpongeBob's life. // Pat's out of town and Spongebob is feeling lonely one day so he blows a bubble to keep him company. As he walks around town talking to his friend , everyone thinks he's taking this imaginary friend thing too far and needs help.

55875.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
55875.description: When Squidward accidentally lets SpongeBob eat an exploding pie, he feels guilty and resolves to make SpongeBob's few remaining hours left in the world enjoyable. // Plankton schemes to steal the Krabby patty by disguising himself as Mr. Krabs and infiltrating the Krusty Krab.

62468.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
62468.description: When Sandy goes out of town for a few days, she puts SpongeBob and Patrick in charge of her pet caterpillar. // Mr. Krabs keeps trying new sales gimmicks for the Krusty Krab, but none of them work. SpongeBob comes up with an idea for colored krabby patties, but Mr. Krabs scoffs at him reminding him to leave the creative thinking to him.

62471.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
62471.description: SpongeBob and Patrick go back in time to see the young Mermaidman and Barnacleboy. // SpongeBob and Patrick watch their heroes fight bad guys in a classic Mermaidman and Barnacleboy episode.

62472.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
62472.description: Squidward bets SpongeBob he can't go a day without crying. // Mrs. Puff has to work through her summer break at the Krusty Krab.

62479.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
62479.description: When Squidward points out to SpongeBob that he's not normal, SpongeBob makes it his mission to become normal. // SpongeBob wakes up one morning to find that everyone in Bikini Bottom is gone - even Gary!

62480.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
62480.description: While working at the Krusty Krab, SpongeBob accidentally gets a splinter. // SpongeBob and Patrick are having fun with their new slide whistles, and, of course, it's driving Squidward crazy.

62481.title: SpongeBob SquarePants

88323.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
88323.description: The long-lost episode of Mermaid Man is finally showing on TV, but will SpongeBob make it home in time to watch? // Karen gets a computer virus, and it's up to SpongeBob to get it out of her!

88324.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
88324.description: When a gang of kids steals the Krusty Krab's grill, SpongeBob and Mr. Krabs go to extreme lengths to win it back. // SpongeBob helps out the Krusty Krab's night shift crew, but the customers crave something creepier than usual.

88331.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
88331.description: It's Sunday in Bikini Bottom, and all Squidward wants to do is enjoy the last few hours of "me time" before the work week begins. But SpongeBob and Patrick continue to intrude on his perfect Sunday. // When a Skill Crane is installed in the Krusty Krab, Squidward becomes obsessed with winning a stuffed animal from the machine. It's not long before he spends all of his money and the deed to his house - and still can't win.

88332.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
88332.description: Mr. Krabs sells his restaurant to a conglomerate that plans to turn the Krusty Krab into a big corporate chain. At first the sell out brings the kind of peace and quiet Krabs always wanted. // Squidward has had enough of SpongeBob's incessant laughter, so he tricks his neighbor into believing that SpongeBob has a laugh-related illness.

88333.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
88333.description: When SpongeBob and Patrick accidentally destroy Sandy's air supply, they have to help her find more oxygen. // SpongeBob wants to earn his belt from karate master Fuzzy Acorns. Will Sandy be able to help?

88340.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
88340.description: Mr. Krabs' Mom is dating again, and it seems like things could be serious. Krabs tries to be happy for his mother, but he is absolutely horrified when he learns that the secret paramour is his arch-rival Plankton! // The adventures of Mermaid Man and Barnacle Boy are being told in a thrilling new motion picture. But as SpongeBob and Patrick soon learn, their heroes are not in the movie.

88341.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
88341.description: During a day of jelly fishing, Patrick gets conked on the head and loses consciousness. When he comes to, the starfish is suddenly speaking in complete sentences - and making sense! // Sandy's experimental teleportation device malfunctions, melding SpongeBob and Squidward into one body. This makes working in the kitchen and behind the check out counter at the Krusty Krab a bit of an issue.

88342.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
88342.description: In another attempt to make more money, Mr. Krabs decides to turn the Krusty Krabs into Krusty Towers, an upscale hotel where the customer is king. // Word of SpongeBob's record of failed boating tests has traveled to the top of the boating school industry. With such a huge blight on Mrs. Puff's teaching record, she is fired from her post.

88350.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
88350.description: The Chimpanzee beneficiaries of Sandy's undersea treedome are paying a visit to see what progress she has made with her inventions. But Sandy doesn't think any of her work will satisfy the chimps. // The Flying Dutchman takes up residence at SpongeBob's house where he proceeds to scare, startle and surprise SpongeBob around the clock.

88351.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
88351.description: Mr. Krabs wants to give his daughter Pearl the best birthday ever. While he works on the party, SpongeBob is assigned the task of figuring out what Pearl would like for a present. // SpongeBob receives an invitation to take part in a competition on mysterious Karate Island for the chance to be crowned "King of Karate".

88352.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
88352.description: During an intense day on the job, SpongeBob's spatula breaks mid patty-flip. With his favorite kitchen implement out of commission, SpongeBob searches for a temporary replacement. // When a wishing well is installed near the Krusty Krab, Mr. Krabs sends SpongeBob down in a bucket to collect the coins that will be dropped by people making their wishes.

94164.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94164.description: SpongeBob and Patrick play Hide N' Seek and SpongeBob searches the world for Patrick. // Plankton masquerades as Gary to steal the Krabby Patty formula.

94165.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94165.description: Squidward sculpts a statue of Mr. Krabs for The Krusty Krab. // Giant sea whelks terrorize the folks of Bikini Bottom.

94172.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94172.description: SpongeBob is left in charge of the Krusty Krab while Mr. Krabs steps out for 15 minutes, and he is determined to make it the best-managed 15 minutes ever! / SpongeBob's got a full day, and he's determined to do everything he's scheduled to do: help fix Mr. Krabs' telescope, go to Patrick's birthday party, and help with Sandy's science presentation.

94173.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94173.description: Patrick is sick of all of his friends not being able to play with him because they have to put on their Krusty Krab hats and go to work. // A new toy store has opened up in Bikini Bottom, and SpongeBob and Patrick couldn’t be happier! In fact, they are having so much fun at the toy store that they accidentally get locked in when it closes.

94174.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94174.description: A friendly day of building sand castles soon turns into all out war when SpongeBob and Patrick use their sand creations to battle each other. // Gary desperately needs a new shell, but all the shells on the market are either too expensive or too fragile. And when SpongeBob tries to find other alternatives to real shells, nothing else seems to work.

94189.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94189.description: When SpongeBob and Patrick accidentally destroy Sandy's air supply, they have to help her find more oxygen. // SpongeBob wants to earn his belt from karate master Fuzzy Acorns. Will Sandy be able to help?

94190.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94190.description: Mr. Krabs' Mom is dating again, and it seems like things could be serious. Krabs tries to be happy for his mother, but he is absolutely horrified when he learns that the secret paramour is his arch-rival Plankton! // The adventures of Mermaid Man and Barnacle Boy are being told in a thrilling new motion picture. But as SpongeBob and Patrick soon learn, their heroes are not in the movie.

94191.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94191.description: During a day of jelly fishing, Patrick gets conked on the head and loses consciousness. When he comes to, the starfish is suddenly speaking in complete sentences - and making sense! // Sandy's experimental teleportation device malfunctions, melding SpongeBob and Squidward into one body. This makes working in the kitchen and behind the check out counter at the Krusty Krab a bit of an issue.

94198.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94198.description: SpongeBob visits his old pal Bubble Buddy's hometown... Bubbletown! // Sandy invites Karen and Mrs. Puff out for a night on the town, so the ladies decide to blow off some steam.

94199.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94199.description: SpongeBob and Patrick have their peaceful day of jelly fishing disturbed by Sandy's competitive nature. // SpongeBob pulls from Squidward's shirt a loose string that never seems to end.

94200.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94200.description: Encouraged by his best friend, Patrick Starfish, SpongeBob overcomes his fears and finally applies for that dream job as a fry cook at the Krusty Krab. // Finding the perfect use for his electric, high powered reef blower, SpongeBob goes to work. Squidward has no idea what chaos lay in store for his quiet afternoon at home. // When SpongeBob meets Sandy Cheeks for the first time, she invites him over to her glass enclosed home. SpongeBob finds the bio dome is full of air, something he's never experienced before.

94207.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94207.description: In the battle for fast food supremacy, Plankton has decided to throw in the towel and start a new business selling trinkets and souvenir gifts. He even renames his store from The Chum Bucket to The Chumporium. // Gary starts biting everyone in town, starting with Squidward. When Squid asks if Gary has been up-to-date on all of his snail shots, SpongeBob reveals that he's never done any of that before.

94208.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94208.description: Mr. Krabs is about to be fined for unfair labor practices. It turns out that in all the years he has been working at the Krusty Krab, SpongeBob has never taken a vacation. // SpongeBob finds an old powdered wig in the trash and wears it around town thinking it is the height of all things cool. The townspeople laugh at him, and Mr. Krabs makes him wear a ridiculous hairnet.

94209.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94209.description: When Squidward swallows his clarinet reed Sandy offers to retrieve the piece by shrinking herself and a mini sub down to microscopic proportions and traveling into Squid's body. // A misunderstanding over a vacation getaway advertisement causes Patrick to think he must "get out of town" or face dire consequences.

94216.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94216.description: After a freak bicycling accident, Squidward is coated in so much mud, leaves, and gunk to make him totally unrecognizable. The residents of Bikini Bottom think that Squidward is some sort of monster come to terrorize the town. // After practicing all day with his brand new magic kit, SpongeBob tries to impress Squidward with his newfound abilities. Of course Squidward, being the ever reluctant participant, sneaks away without SpongeBob noticing.

94217.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94217.description: SpongeBob has failed his driving test - again. Pat is so outraged by the injustice of it all that he storms into the testing facility and takes the test to prove that it is an unfair test and impossible to pass. // An oversight in a Royal genealogy document reveals that Patrick is the next in line to receive a kingly title. It's not long before the power of the crown goes straight to the starfish's head.

94218.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94218.description: A concert promoter wants to send SpongeBob and Squidward on the road, until greedy Mr. Krabs decides to manage them—and their “world tour”—himself.

94226.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94226.description: SpongeBob's favorite jellyfishing net is missing! And worst of all, Pat may have been the one that stole it. // Rejected yet again by Squidward, SpongeBob decides that if he can't hang with the real Squid, he'll make his own. So SpongeBob builds a ventriloquist dummy modeled after his favorite neighbor.

94227.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
94227.description: In an attempt to get away from SpongeBob, Squidward drives off in his boat as fast as he can, but he is pulled over and ordered to go to boating school. // Mr. Krabs decides to go into the tabloid business.
